HEADWORD: Purpuriparous
<hw>Pur`pu*rip"a*rous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>purpura</ets> purple + <ets>parere</ets> to produce.]</ety>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Producing, or connected with, a purple-colored
secretion; <as>as, the <ex>purpuriparous</ex> gland of certain
gastropods</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

